2. What Data We Collect
We collect the minimum data necessary for app functionality and user experience. Data collected falls into the following categories:
2.1 Personal Data
•	Provided Directly: When you voluntarily provide data, such as your name, email address, or contact details for feedback or inquiries.
•	Purpose: To communicate with you, send app-related updates, or resolve inquiries.
2.2 Non-Personal Data
•	Automatically Collected:
o	Device information (e.g., device type, operating system).
o	App usage statistics (e.g., session duration, navigation patterns).
o	Crash reports to improve app performance.
2.3 Cookies and Analytics Data
•	We may use analytics tools such as Google Analytics to collect anonymised data for app performance monitoring and improvements. These tools may use cookies or similar technologies to gather data.
________________________________________
3. How We Use Your Data
We use the collected data to:
•	Enhance app functionality and user experience.
•	Provide support for inquiries or technical issues.
•	Analyse app usage trends to optimise features.
•	Send updates or notifications about the app.
We will not use your data for any purposes beyond those stated without your explicit consent.
________________________________________
4. How We Share Your Data
We do not sell or rent your data. Data may be shared under the following circumstances:
•	Service Providers: Trusted third parties (e.g., analytics providers) who assist in improving app performance.
•	Legal Obligations: To comply with legal requirements or respond to lawful requests from government authorities.
________________________________________
5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
The app may use cookies or similar technologies to:
•	Understand usage patterns.
•	Improve functionality and user experience.
You can manage cookies and similar technologies through your device or browser settings.
________________________________________
6. Data Security
We take reasonable precautions to protect your data, including:
•	Encryption: Data is encrypted during transmission where applicable.
•	Secure Storage: Data is stored in secure environments.
•	Access Control: Only authorised personnel can access collected data.
However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure.
________________________________________
7. Data Retention and Deletion
We retain your data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy.
•	Non-Personal Data: Retained indefinitely for analytics.
•	Personal Data: Retained until you request its deletion.
To request data deletion, contact us at afczim@gmail.com.
________________________________________
8. Your Rights
Under applicable privacy laws, including GDPR, you have the following rights:
•	Access: Request access to your data.
•	Correction: Request correction of inaccurate data.
•	Deletion: Request deletion of your data.
•	Objection: Object to specific data processing activities.
•	Portability: Request transfer of your data to another service provider.
To exercise your rights, contact us at afczim@gmail.com.
________________________________________
9. Children’s Privacy
The AFC Hymns Collection app is not intended for users under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If you believe we have collected such data, contact us at afczim@gmail.com for immediate deletion.
________________________________________
10. Third-Party Links
The app may include links to external websites or services (e.g., YouTube). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of third-party platforms. Please review their privacy policies.
________________________________________
11. International Data Transfers
Data may be processed in locations outside your country of residence. We ensure that such transfers comply with applicable laws, including GDPR, using legal mechanisms such as Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) or explicit consent.
________________________________________
12. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes will be posted within the app and on the app’s store listing. Continued use of the app after updates indicates acceptance of the revised policy.
